# Only input.env + golden-*.txt are committed per scenario. Everything the
# builder materializes at (re)build time — the seeded stats.db / cache.db
# (+ WAL/SHM sidecars) and the fake HOME's .local data dir (config.json
# included) — is regenerated into a scratch dir by bin/cctally-budget-test
# and bin/cctally-reconcile-test, and must never land in the tree (would leak
# host-dependent SQLite bytes + dirty on every rebuild). This is the
# `--out` scratch consumption class: the committed DBs are never read, so
# committing them only invites stale drift. Goldens carry only rendered
# text + the VERSION-normalized share artifacts, so they stay location- and
# release-stable.
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*/.local/
